{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"We're here to celebrate compassion."},{"time":2000,"text":"But compassion, from my vantage point,"},{"time":4000,"text":"has a problem."},{"time":6000,"text":"As essential as it is across our traditions,"},{"time":9000,"text":"as real as so many of us know it to be"},{"time":11000,"text":"in particular lives,"},{"time":13000,"text":"the word \"compassion\" is hollowed out in our culture,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and it is suspect in my field of journalism."},{"time":19000,"text":"It's seen as a squishy kumbaya thing,"},{"time":22000,"text":"or it's seen as potentially depressing."},{"time":25000,"text":"Karen Armstrong has told what I think is an iconic story"},{"time":28000,"text":"of giving a speech in Holland"},{"time":30000,"text":"and, after the fact, the word \"compassion\""},{"time":33000,"text":"was translated as \"pity.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"Now compassion, when it enters the news,"},{"time":39000,"text":"too often comes in the form"},{"time":41000,"text":"of feel-good feature pieces"},{"time":43000,"text":"or sidebars about heroic people"},{"time":46000,"text":"you could never be like"},{"time":48000,"text":"or happy endings"},{"time":50000,"text":"or examples of self-sacrifice"},{"time":53000,"text":"that would seem to be too good to be true"},{"time":55000,"text":"most of the time."},{"time":57000,"text":"Our cultural imagination about compassion"},{"time":60000,"text":"has been deadened by idealistic images."},{"time":63000,"text":"And so what I'd like to do this morning"},{"time":65000,"text":"for the next few minutes"},{"time":67000,"text":"is perform a linguistic resurrection."},{"time":69000,"text":"And I hope you'll come with me on my basic premise"},{"time":71000,"text":"that words matter,"},{"time":73000,"text":"that they shape the way we understand ourselves,"},{"time":75000,"text":"the way we interpret the world"},{"time":77000,"text":"and the way we treat others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"When this country"},{"time":81000,"text":"first encountered genuine diversity"},{"time":83000,"text":"in the 1960s,"},{"time":85000,"text":"we adopted tolerance"},{"time":87000,"text":"as the core civic virtue"},{"time":89000,"text":"with which we would approach that."},{"time":91000,"text":"Now the word \"tolerance,\" if you look at it in the dictionary,"},{"time":94000,"text":"connotes \"allowing,\" \"indulging\""},{"time":97000,"text":"and \"enduring.\""},{"time":99000,"text":"In the medical context that it comes from,"},{"time":101000,"text":"it is about testing the limits of thriving"},{"time":104000,"text":"in an unfavorable environment."},{"time":107000,"text":"Tolerance is not really a lived virtue;"},{"time":109000,"text":"it's more of a cerebral ascent."},{"time":112000,"text":"And it's too cerebral"},{"time":114000,"text":"to animate guts and hearts"},{"time":116000,"text":"and behavior"},{"time":118000,"text":"when the going gets rough."},{"time":120000,"text":"And the going is pretty rough right now."},{"time":122000,"text":"I think that without perhaps being able to name it,"},{"time":125000,"text":"we are collectively experiencing"},{"time":127000,"text":"that we've come as far as we can"},{"time":129000,"text":"with tolerance as our only guiding virtue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"Compassion is a worthy successor."},{"time":135000,"text":"It is organic,"},{"time":137000,"text":"across our religious, spiritual and ethical traditions,"},{"time":140000,"text":"and yet it transcends them."},{"time":143000,"text":"Compassion is a piece of vocabulary"},{"time":146000,"text":"that could change us if we truly let it sink into"},{"time":149000,"text":"the standards to which we hold ourselves and others,"},{"time":152000,"text":"both in our private and in our civic spaces."},{"time":156000,"text":"So what is it, three-dimensionally?"},{"time":159000,"text":"What are its kindred and component parts?"},{"time":162000,"text":"What's in its universe of attendant virtues?"},{"time":164000,"text":"To start simply,"},{"time":166000,"text":"I want to say that compassion is kind."},{"time":169000,"text":"Now \"kindness\" might sound like a very mild word,"},{"time":173000,"text":"and it's prone to its own abundant cliche."},{"time":177000,"text":"But kindness is an everyday byproduct"},{"time":179000,"text":"of all the great virtues."},{"time":181000,"text":"And it is a most edifying form"},{"time":183000,"text":"of instant gratification."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"Compassion is also curious."},{"time":189000,"text":"Compassion cultivates and practices curiosity."},{"time":192000,"text":"I love a phrase that was offered me"},{"time":194000,"text":"by two young women"},{"time":196000,"text":"who are interfaith innovators in Los Angeles,"},{"time":198000,"text":"Aziza Hasan and Malka Fenyvesi."},{"time":201000,"text":"They are working to create a new imagination"},{"time":203000,"text":"about shared life among young Jews and Muslims,"},{"time":206000,"text":"and as they do that, they cultivate what they call"},{"time":209000,"text":"\"curiosity without assumptions.\""},{"time":211000,"text":"Well that's going to be a breeding ground for compassion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"Compassion can be synonymous with empathy."},{"time":218000,"text":"It can be joined with the harder work"},{"time":221000,"text":"of forgiveness and reconciliation,"},{"time":224000,"text":"but it can also express itself"},{"time":226000,"text":"in the simple act of presence."},{"time":229000,"text":"It's linked to practical virtues"},{"time":231000,"text":"like generosity and hospitality"},{"time":234000,"text":"and just being there,"},{"time":236000,"text":"just showing up."},{"time":240000,"text":"I think that compassion"},{"time":242000,"text":"also is often linked to beauty --"},{"time":244000,"text":"and by that I mean a willingness"},{"time":246000,"text":"to see beauty in the other,"},{"time":248000,"text":"not just what it is about them"},{"time":250000,"text":"that might need helping."},{"time":252000,"text":"I love it that my Muslim conversation partners"},{"time":255000,"text":"often speak of beauty as a core moral value."},{"time":259000,"text":"And in that light, for the religious,"},{"time":262000,"text":"compassion also brings us"},{"time":264000,"text":"into the territory of mystery --"},{"time":267000,"text":"encouraging us not just"},{"time":269000,"text":"to see beauty,"},{"time":271000,"text":"but perhaps also to look for the face of God"},{"time":273000,"text":"in the moment of suffering,"},{"time":275000,"text":"in the face of a stranger,"},{"time":277000,"text":"in the face of the vibrant religious other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"I'm not sure if I can show you"},{"time":283000,"text":"what tolerance looks like,"},{"time":285000,"text":"but I can show you what compassion looks like --"},{"time":287000,"text":"because it is visible."},{"time":289000,"text":"When we see it, we recognize it"},{"time":291000,"text":"and it changes the way we think about what is doable,"},{"time":293000,"text":"what is possible."},{"time":295000,"text":"It is so important"},{"time":297000,"text":"when we're communicating big ideas --"},{"time":299000,"text":"but especially a big spiritual idea like compassion --"},{"time":303000,"text":"to root it as we present it to others"},{"time":305000,"text":"in space and time and flesh and blood --"},{"time":308000,"text":"the color and complexity of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"And compassion does seek physicality."},{"time":316000,"text":"I first started to learn this most vividly"},{"time":318000,"text":"from Matthew Sanford."},{"time":320000,"text":"And I don't imagine that you will realize this"},{"time":322000,"text":"when you look at this photograph of him,"},{"time":324000,"text":"but he's paraplegic."},{"time":326000,"text":"He's been paralyzed from the waist down since he was 13,"},{"time":329000,"text":"in a car crash that killed his father and his sister."},{"time":332000,"text":"Matthew's legs don't work, and he'll never walk again,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and -- and he does experience this as an \"and\""},{"time":337000,"text":"rather than a \"but\" --"},{"time":339000,"text":"and he experiences himself"},{"time":341000,"text":"to be healed and whole."},{"time":343000,"text":"And as a teacher of yoga,"},{"time":345000,"text":"he brings that experience to others"},{"time":347000,"text":"across the spectrum of ability and disability,"},{"time":350000,"text":"health, illness and aging."},{"time":352000,"text":"He says that he's just at an extreme end"},{"time":354000,"text":"of the spectrum we're all on."},{"time":357000,"text":"He's doing some amazing work now"},{"time":360000,"text":"with veterans coming back from Iraq and Afghanistan."},{"time":363000,"text":"And Matthew has made this remarkable observation"},{"time":366000,"text":"that I'm just going to offer you and let it sit."},{"time":369000,"text":"I can't quite explain it, and he can't either."},{"time":372000,"text":"But he says that he has yet to experience someone"},{"time":375000,"text":"who became more aware of their body,"},{"time":378000,"text":"in all its frailty and its grace,"},{"time":381000,"text":"without, at the same time,"},{"time":383000,"text":"becoming more compassionate towards all of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"Compassion also looks like this."},{"time":389000,"text":"This is Jean Vanier."},{"time":392000,"text":"Jean Vanier helped found the L'Arche communities,"},{"time":394000,"text":"which you can now find all over the world,"},{"time":396000,"text":"communities centered around life"},{"time":398000,"text":"with people with mental disabilities --"},{"time":400000,"text":"mostly Down syndrome."},{"time":402000,"text":"The communities that Jean Vanier founded,"},{"time":404000,"text":"like Jean Vanier himself,"},{"time":406000,"text":"exude tenderness."},{"time":408000,"text":"\"Tender\" is another word"},{"time":410000,"text":"I would love to spend some time resurrecting."},{"time":412000,"text":"We spend so much time in this culture"},{"time":414000,"text":"being driven and aggressive,"},{"time":417000,"text":"and I spend a lot of time being those things too."},{"time":419000,"text":"And compassion can also have those qualities."},{"time":422000,"text":"But again and again, lived compassion"},{"time":425000,"text":"brings us back to the wisdom of tenderness."},{"time":429000,"text":"Jean Vanier says"},{"time":431000,"text":"that his work,"},{"time":433000,"text":"like the work of other people --"},{"time":435000,"text":"his great, beloved, late friend Mother Teresa --"},{"time":438000,"text":"is never in the first instance about changing the world;"},{"time":440000,"text":"it's in the first instance about changing ourselves."},{"time":443000,"text":"He's says that what they do with L'Arche"},{"time":446000,"text":"is not a solution, but a sign."},{"time":449000,"text":"Compassion is rarely a solution,"},{"time":452000,"text":"but it is always a sign of a deeper reality,"},{"time":454000,"text":"of deeper human possibilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457000,"text":"And compassion is unleashed"},{"time":460000,"text":"in wider and wider circles"},{"time":463000,"text":"by signs and stories,"},{"time":465000,"text":"never by statistics and strategies."},{"time":468000,"text":"We need those things too,"},{"time":470000,"text":"but we're also bumping up against their limits."},{"time":473000,"text":"And at the same time that we are doing that,"},{"time":476000,"text":"I think we are rediscovering the power of story --"},{"time":479000,"text":"that as human beings, we need stories"},{"time":481000,"text":"to survive, to flourish,"},{"time":483000,"text":"to change."},{"time":485000,"text":"Our traditions have always known this,"},{"time":487000,"text":"and that is why they have always cultivated stories at their heart"},{"time":490000,"text":"and carried them forward in time for us."},{"time":493000,"text":"There is, of course, a story"},{"time":496000,"text":"behind the key moral longing"},{"time":498000,"text":"and commandment of Judaism"},{"time":500000,"text":"to repair the world -- tikkun olam."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503000,"text":"And I'll never forget hearing that story"},{"time":505000,"text":"from Dr. Rachel Naomi Remen,"},{"time":507000,"text":"who told it to me as her grandfather told it to her,"},{"time":510000,"text":"that in the beginning of the Creation"},{"time":512000,"text":"something happened"},{"time":514000,"text":"and the original light of the universe"},{"time":516000,"text":"was shattered into countless pieces."},{"time":518000,"text":"It lodged as shards"},{"time":520000,"text":"inside every aspect of the Creation."},{"time":522000,"text":"And that the highest human calling"},{"time":525000,"text":"is to look for this light, to point at it when we see it,"},{"time":528000,"text":"to gather it up,"},{"time":530000,"text":"and in so doing, to repair the world."},{"time":533000,"text":"Now this might sound like a fanciful tale."},{"time":536000,"text":"Some of my fellow journalists might interpret it that way."},{"time":539000,"text":"Rachel Naomi Remen says"},{"time":541000,"text":"this is an important and empowering story"},{"time":543000,"text":"for our time,"},{"time":545000,"text":"because this story insists"},{"time":547000,"text":"that each and every one of us,"},{"time":549000,"text":"frail and flawed as we may be,"},{"time":551000,"text":"inadequate as we may feel,"},{"time":553000,"text":"has exactly what's needed"},{"time":555000,"text":"to help repair the part of the world"},{"time":558000,"text":"that we can see and touch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"Stories like this,"},{"time":564000,"text":"signs like this,"},{"time":566000,"text":"are practical tools"},{"time":568000,"text":"in a world longing to bring compassion"},{"time":572000,"text":"to abundant images of suffering"},{"time":575000,"text":"that can otherwise overwhelm us."},{"time":578000,"text":"Rachel Naomi Remen"},{"time":580000,"text":"is actually bringing compassion"},{"time":582000,"text":"back to its rightful place alongside science"},{"time":584000,"text":"in her field of medicine"},{"time":586000,"text":"in the training of new doctors."},{"time":589000,"text":"And this trend"},{"time":591000,"text":"of what Rachel Naomi Remen is doing,"},{"time":593000,"text":"how these kinds of virtues"},{"time":595000,"text":"are finding a place in the vocabulary of medicine --"},{"time":597000,"text":"the work Fred Luskin is doing --"},{"time":599000,"text":"I think this is one of the most fascinating developments"},{"time":601000,"text":"of the 21st century --"},{"time":603000,"text":"that science, in fact,"},{"time":605000,"text":"is taking a virtue like compassion"},{"time":608000,"text":"definitively out of the realm of idealism."},{"time":611000,"text":"This is going to change science, I believe,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and it will change religion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"But here's a face"},{"time":618000,"text":"from 20th century science"},{"time":620000,"text":"that might surprise you"},{"time":622000,"text":"in a discussion about compassion."},{"time":624000,"text":"We all know about the Albert Einstein"},{"time":627000,"text":"who came up with E = mc2."},{"time":630000,"text":"We don't hear so much about the Einstein"},{"time":633000,"text":"who invited the African American opera singer, Marian Anderson,"},{"time":636000,"text":"to stay in his home when she came to sing in Princeton"},{"time":639000,"text":"because the best hotel there"},{"time":641000,"text":"was segregated and wouldn't have her."},{"time":643000,"text":"We don't hear about the Einstein who used his celebrity"},{"time":646000,"text":"to advocate for political prisoners in Europe"},{"time":649000,"text":"or the Scottsboro boys"},{"time":651000,"text":"in the American South."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653000,"text":"Einstein believed deeply"},{"time":656000,"text":"that science should transcend"},{"time":658000,"text":"national and ethnic divisions."},{"time":660000,"text":"But he watched physicists and chemists"},{"time":663000,"text":"become the purveyors of weapons of mass destruction"},{"time":666000,"text":"in the early 20th century."},{"time":668000,"text":"He once said that science in his generation"},{"time":671000,"text":"had become like a razor blade"},{"time":673000,"text":"in the hands of a three-year-old."},{"time":675000,"text":"And Einstein foresaw"},{"time":677000,"text":"that as we grow more modern"},{"time":679000,"text":"and technologically advanced,"},{"time":681000,"text":"we need the virtues"},{"time":683000,"text":"our traditions carry forward in time"},{"time":686000,"text":"more, not less."},{"time":688000,"text":"He liked to talk about the spiritual geniuses of the ages."},{"time":692000,"text":"Some of his favorites were Moses,"},{"time":694000,"text":"Jesus, Buddha, St. Francis of Assisi,"},{"time":697000,"text":"Gandhi -- he adored his contemporary, Gandhi."},{"time":700000,"text":"And Einstein said --"},{"time":702000,"text":"and I think this is a quote,"},{"time":704000,"text":"again, that has not been passed down in his legacy --"},{"time":706000,"text":"that \"these kinds of people"},{"time":708000,"text":"are geniuses in the art of living,"},{"time":710000,"text":"more necessary"},{"time":712000,"text":"to the dignity, security and joy of humanity"},{"time":715000,"text":"than the discoverers of objective knowledge.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":720000,"text":"Now invoking Einstein"},{"time":722000,"text":"might not seem the best way to bring compassion down to earth"},{"time":725000,"text":"and make it seem accessible to all the rest of us,"},{"time":727000,"text":"but actually it is."},{"time":730000,"text":"I want to show you"},{"time":732000,"text":"the rest of this photograph,"},{"time":735000,"text":"because this photograph"},{"time":737000,"text":"is analogous to what we do to the word \"compassion\" in our culture --"},{"time":740000,"text":"we clean it up"},{"time":742000,"text":"and we diminish its depths and its grounding"},{"time":745000,"text":"in life, which is messy."},{"time":747000,"text":"So in this photograph"},{"time":749000,"text":"you see a mind looking out a window"},{"time":751000,"text":"at what might be a cathedral -- it's not."},{"time":753000,"text":"This is the full photograph,"},{"time":755000,"text":"and you see a middle-aged man wearing a leather jacket,"},{"time":757000,"text":"smoking a cigar."},{"time":759000,"text":"And by the look of that paunch,"},{"time":761000,"text":"he hasn't been doing enough yoga."},{"time":763000,"text":"We put these two photographs side-by-side on our website,"},{"time":766000,"text":"and someone said, \"When I look at the first photo,"},{"time":768000,"text":"I ask myself, what was he thinking?"},{"time":770000,"text":"And when I look at the second, I ask,"},{"time":772000,"text":"what kind of person was he? What kind of man is this?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"Well, he was complicated."},{"time":777000,"text":"He was incredibly compassionate"},{"time":779000,"text":"in some of his relationships"},{"time":781000,"text":"and terribly inadequate in others."},{"time":784000,"text":"And it is much harder, often,"},{"time":787000,"text":"to be compassionate towards those closest to us,"},{"time":791000,"text":"which is another quality in the universe of compassion,"},{"time":794000,"text":"on its dark side,"},{"time":796000,"text":"that also deserves our serious attention and illumination."},{"time":801000,"text":"Gandhi, too, was a real flawed human being."},{"time":804000,"text":"So was Martin Luther King, Jr. So was Dorothy Day."},{"time":807000,"text":"So was Mother Teresa."},{"time":809000,"text":"So are we all."},{"time":811000,"text":"And I want to say"},{"time":813000,"text":"that it is a liberating thing"},{"time":815000,"text":"to realize that that is no obstacle to compassion --"},{"time":817000,"text":"following on what Fred Luskin says --"},{"time":820000,"text":"that these flaws just make us human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"Our culture is obsessed with perfection"},{"time":826000,"text":"and with hiding problems."},{"time":828000,"text":"But what a liberating thing to realize"},{"time":830000,"text":"that our problems, in fact,"},{"time":832000,"text":"are probably our richest sources"},{"time":835000,"text":"for rising to this ultimate virtue of compassion,"},{"time":839000,"text":"towards bringing compassion"},{"time":841000,"text":"towards the suffering and joys of others."},{"time":845000,"text":"Rachel Naomi Remen is a better doctor"},{"time":848000,"text":"because of her life-long struggle with Crohn's disease."},{"time":850000,"text":"Einstein became a humanitarian,"},{"time":852000,"text":"not because of his exquisite knowledge"},{"time":854000,"text":"of space and time and matter,"},{"time":856000,"text":"but because he was a Jew as Germany grew fascist."},{"time":859000,"text":"And Karen Armstrong, I think you would also say"},{"time":862000,"text":"that it was some of your very wounding experiences"},{"time":865000,"text":"in a religious life that,"},{"time":867000,"text":"with a zigzag,"},{"time":869000,"text":"have led to the Charter for Compassion."},{"time":873000,"text":"Compassion can't be reduced to sainthood"},{"time":876000,"text":"any more than it can be reduced to pity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880000,"text":"So I want to propose"},{"time":882000,"text":"a final definition of compassion --"},{"time":885000,"text":"this is Einstein with Paul Robeson by the way --"},{"time":888000,"text":"and that would be for us"},{"time":890000,"text":"to call compassion a spiritual technology."},{"time":894000,"text":"Now our traditions contain"},{"time":896000,"text":"vast wisdom about this,"},{"time":898000,"text":"and we need them to mine it for us now."},{"time":901000,"text":"But compassion is also equally at home"},{"time":904000,"text":"in the secular as in the religious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907000,"text":"So I will paraphrase Einstein in closing"},{"time":910000,"text":"and say that humanity,"},{"time":912000,"text":"the future of humanity,"},{"time":914000,"text":"needs this technology"},{"time":916000,"text":"as much as it needs all the others"},{"time":918000,"text":"that have now connected us"},{"time":921000,"text":"and set before us"},{"time":923000,"text":"the terrifying and wondrous possibility"},{"time":925000,"text":"of actually becoming one human race."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}